c: 28
v: 48
t: "And yet, now that the truth has come to them from Us (through a Messenger), still they say (by way of an excuse for their denial of it), \"Why has he not been granted the like of what Moses was granted (all at once)?\" Did they not preject previously belief refuse to believe in what had been granted to Moses? They said: \"Both are sorcery, each supporting the other.\" They also said: \"In each we are unbelievers"